<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="NAME"
>NAME <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Crypt::RSA::Errorhandler - Error handling mechanism for Crypt::RSA.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="SYNOPSIS"
>SYNOPSIS <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<pre class="sh_perl">    package Foo;

    use Crypt::RSA::Errorhandler;
    @ISA = qw(Crypt::RSA::Errorhandler);
    
    sub alive { 
        ..
        ..
        return 
        $self-&#62;error (&#34;Awake, awake! Ring the alarum bell. \
                       Murther and treason!&#34;, $dagger) 
            if $self-&#62;murdered($king);
    }


    package main; 

    use Foo;
    my $foo = new Foo;
    $foo-&#62;alive($king) or print $foo-&#62;errstr(); 
        # prints &#34;Awake, awake! ... &#34;</pre>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="DESCRIPTION"
>DESCRIPTION <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Crypt::RSA::Errorhandler encapsulates the error handling mechanism used by the modules in Crypt::RSA bundle. Crypt::RSA::Errorhandler doesn&#39;t have a constructor and is meant to be inherited. The derived modules use its two methods, error() and errstr(), to communicate error messages to the caller.</p>

<p>When a method of the derived module fails, it calls $self-&#62;error() and returns undef to the caller. The error message passed to error() is made available to the caller through the errstr() accessor. error() also accepts a list of sensitive data that it wipes out (undef&#39;es) before returning.</p>

<p>The caller should <b>never</b> call errstr() to check for errors. errstr() should be called only when a method indicates (usually through an undef return value) that an error has occured. This is because errstr() is never overwritten and will always contain a value after the occurance of first error.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="METHODS"
>METHODS <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<dl>
<dt><a name='new'></a><a name="new()"
><b>new()</b></a></dt>

<dd>
<p>Barebones constructor.</p>

<dt><a name='error'></a><a name="error($mesage,_($wipeme,_$wipemetoo))"
><b>error($mesage, ($wipeme, $wipemetoo))</b></a></dt>

<dd>
<p>The first argument to error() is $message which is placed in $self- &#62;{errstr} and the remaining arguments are interpretted as variables containing sensitive data that are wiped out from the memory. error() always returns undef.</p>

<dt><a name='errstr'></a><a name="errstr()"
><b>errstr()</b></a></dt>

<dd>
<p>errstr() is an accessor method for $self-&#62;{errstr}.</p>

<dt><a name='errstrrst'></a><a name="errstrrst()"
><b>errstrrst()</b></a></dt>

<dd>
<p>This method sets $self-&#62;{errstr} to an empty string.</p>
</dd>
</dl>

